\fB\-\-colour\fR[=\fI\,WHEN\/\fR]
use markers to highlight the matching strings;
WHEN is `always', `never', or `auto'
.TP
\fB\-U\fR, \fB\-\-binary\fR
do not strip CR characters at EOL (MSDOS)
